<font color="#FF0000">TIME TO BID FAREWELL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan 21 18:57:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I didn't realize how much Viet Nam was still with me, until I stumbled upon this site about 1 month ago.  First I was fascinated, then attracted, then involved, and now TOO involved.  What became a weekly read has become a daily read, and a reminder of an event that changed my life, and the lives of our generation, 20+years ago.  I went back and re read every posting on this site and I have changed my opinion that those bum's with the &quot;I'm hungry, will work for food, Viet Nam Vet, God Bless&quot; signs on the freeway ramps are not all representative of Veterans from Nam.  I found wit and intelligence, stories and good feelings. Alas, I also found personal attacks and those who can't stand to be reminded that they don't think.<br><br>
From a patriotic kid who rushed to get his draft card on his 18th birthday, to a war protestor, drug using street radical, the war and it's aftermath taught me to question authority and to always think critical.  It also taught me self reflection.  When I feel the need to check this site daily, I know the war is again TOO MUCH with me.  It changed me long ago, and I got over it. It is changing me again, and this time, I see that in some of my postings.  Perhaps that is the real legacy of this war, it's ability and power to reach out over 25 years and still stir up something crazy within all of us.<br><br>
Well, Nurse Ratchet was the perfect cue, McMurphy the perfect anti-hero, the psychiatric ward the right stage, and the Chief has just smashed the window open.  So, like the Chief, or perhaps Nixon, taking Checkers out for a walk, I bit you all the best of luck, fond wishes, and happy postings.  I'll look in once in awhile, to make sure that the resistor is still the hero, and the protestor the true patriot, but I need to put my 60's memories back into the drawer, between SDS and the Grateful Dead, and move on.<br><br>
Thank you one and all, for sharing my thoughts, and allowing me the same enjoyment with yours.<br><br>
Dr. Crazy
